        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 2:09PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 209 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Shamrock, or 24 miles south of Fort Morgan, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shamrock.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
